<div id="country3" class="tabcontent">
<div style="width: 740px; border: 1px dashed gray; padding: 10px;  margin:0px auto;">

<h2>Tender Proposal</h2><hr />
<span class="title">Screen Overview </span><br />
This screen captures the details of tender proposal. Tender proposal screen is used before tender creation. Based on future requirement for department tender proposal entry is done by purchase department.
<br /><hr /><br />

<img src="images/Pro_tenderproposal.jpg" width="725"  /><br /><br />
<hr />

<p>
<span class="title">Department:</span><br />
    Login department name will be displayed by the system.
<br />
<span class="title">Import Last Proposal (Button): </span> <br />
   By clicking on import last proposal button last proposal data will be displayed in grid. User can update the tender qty or delete the selected row.
<br />
    <span class="title">Select Group:</span> 
    <br />If user wants to create tender proposal from previous tender then select the item group from the list. 

<br />
    <span class="title">Select Tender No.: </span> 
    <br />Select Tender no. from the list.

<br />
    <span class="title">OK (Button): </span> 
    <br />By clicking on OK button selected tender data will be displayed in grid. User can update the tender qty or delete the selected row.

<br />
    <span class="title">PVMS/NIV: </span> 
    <br />If user wants to search for any PVMS or NIV item then write PVMS/NIV code and click on search button.

<br />
    <span class="title">Add (Button):</span> 
    <br />By clicking on Add button selected tender data will be displayed in grid. User can select item, change qty.
    
    <br />
    <span class="title">Update (Button):	 </span> 
    <br />By clicking on Update button changed data will be update.
    
    <br />
    <span class="title">Delete (Button):	 </span> 
    <br />By clicking on Delete button selected row in grid will be deleted.
    
    <br />
    <span class="title">Print (Button):	</span> 
    <br />By clicking on Print button Proposal will be printed.
     
</p>

</div>
</body>
